<TD VALIGN=TOP COLSPAN=2>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<CENTER><H2><FONT COLOR="red">PART I: DOMESTIC POLICY ISSUES</FONT></H2></CENTER>
<P><B>CHAPTER I<BR>
<DD>Moving an Agenda Through Congress</B><BR>
<DD><I>David M. Mason</I>	
<P>
<CENTER><H2><FONT COLOR="red"><I>The Proper Role of the Federal Government</I></FONT></H2></CENTER>
<P><B>CHAPTER 2<BR>
<DD>Restructuring, Closing, and Consolidating Federal Agencies and Programs</B><BR>
<DD><I>Ronald D. Utt</I>	
<P>
<B>CHAPTER 3<BR>
<DD>Transferring Functions to the States</B><BR>
<DD><I>Douglas Seay and Robert E. Moffit</I>	 
<P>
<B>CHAPTER 4<BR>
<DD>Transferring Functions to the Private Sector</B><BR>
<DD><I>Ronald D. Utt </I>		
<P>
<B>CHAPTER 5<BR>
<DD>Empowering Families and Communities</B><BR>
<DD><I>Adam Meyerson </I>	

<P>
<CENTER><H2><FONT COLOR="red"><I>Reforming Two Key Federal Institutions</I></FONT></H2></CENTER>
<P>
<B>CHAPTER 6<BR>
<DD>Downsizing and Improving the Federal Civil Service</B><BR>
<DD><I>Donald J. Devine and Robert E. Moffit</I>
<P>
<B>CHAPTER 7<BR>
<DD>Reining in the Federal Judiciary</B><BR>
<DD><I>Edwin Meese III and Rhett DeHart </I>	
<P>
<CENTER><H2><FONT COLOR="red"><I>Taking the Initiative</I></FONT></H2></CENTER>
<P>
<B>CHAPTER 8<BR>
<DD>Solving the Problem of Middle-Class Entitlements</B><BR>
<DD><I>Stuart M. Butler and John S. Barry	</I>

<P>
<B>CHAPTER 9<BR>
